          "value": "xywh=pixel:831.3601319084764,2907.946498819827,2854.0112292244903,2186.1526357199064"
        }
      },
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "YOU ARE WITH US in our prayer, our love and our doubt,\nin our longing to feel Your Presence and do Your will.\nYou are the still clear voice within us.\nTherefore, O God, when doubt troubles us,\nwhen anxiety makes us tremble,\nwhen pain clouds the mind,\nwe look inward for the answer to our prayers.\nThere may we find You,\nand there find courage, insight and endurance.\nAnd let our worship bring us closer to one another,\nthat all Israel, and all who seek You,\nmay find new strength for Your service.\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה, יְיָ, שֶׁאוֹתְךָ לְבַדְּךָ בְּיִרְאָה נַעֲבֹד.\nBaruch atah, Adonai, she-ot'cha l'vad'cha b'yirah naavod.",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
